[SN]TITLE[SN]
Charlotte Dujardin and Valegro win World Cup final in Lyon

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Britain's Olympic dressage champion Charlotte Dujardin followed Saturday's Grand Prix win with victory in the World Cup final in Lyon on Sunday.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The 28-year-old and her London 2012 horse Valegro took the Freestyle class with a new floor-plan routine and music that scored 92.179%.
Germany's Helen Langehanenberg finished second with 87.339%, and Dutch rider Edward Gal third on 83.696%.
